Ohanaeze Ndigbo Youth Council (OYC) Worldwide has said that  a new Zik of Africa will be presented to Nigerians next year 2021 just as it said that  any attempt to ambush Igbo’s legitimate political interests to produce the president in 2023 will strengthen the agitation of self-determination across the country, as Oduduwa and Biafra The Igbo youth group in a statement on Friday signed by  Mazi Okechukwu Isiguzoro, President General, Ohanaeze Ndigbo Youth Council Worldwide and  Okwu Nnabuike, Secretary General said that  Nigerians especially the youths will ensure that there will be generational shift in 2023, as the next president of Nigeria will not be above 65 years by 2023. Nigeria need a energetic person with vigour to reactivate the full potentials of Nigeria as truly the Giant of Africa the group said. The body went on to say that it was ready to praley the All Progressive Congress (APC) and the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in  about the pitfalls and grave consequences of leadership imposition on Nigerians, and need to respect the gentleman’s agreement of rotational presidency between North and South, though unwritten, but should be respected for the future and sustainable peace in Nigeria. Dokpesi tests positive for coronavirus Ohanaeze Ndigbo Youth Council [OYC] Worldwide had Cautioned the power brokers in APC and PDP, about the pitfalls and grave Consequences of leadership imposition on Nigerians, and need to respect the Gentleman’s Agreement of Rotational Presidency between North and South, though Unwritten, but should be respected for the future and sustainable peace in Nigeria. OYC described Nigeria as a Nation threatened by personal gains of few political leaders against the Collective interests of Nigerians. Any attempt to ambush Igbos, their legitimate political interests to produce president either from South/South or South East in 2023 through political parties tickets, will strengthen the agitation of self-determination across the country, as Oduduwa and Biafra referendum and independence will gather international recognition and make the Future of Nigeria bleak. OYC insists through moral persuasive approach and aggressive Consultative negotiations with Critical stakeholders across the Country, will Commence immediately the Coronavirus Pandemic is Contained in Nigeria, the diaspora Chapters of OYC have been mandated to begin sensitisation programmes and deploy resources for the facilitation of ethnic youth groups, that will accompany Igbo delegation to interface with President Muhammadu Buhari, Governor Nasir El Rufai, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, former president Olusegun Obasanjo and others. Igbo Youths insist every Nigerian has the right to ascribe for the highest office in the land, but the collective interests of Nigeria supersedes the individual quests. God had kept General Yakubu Gowon alive for the singular reason to cement the unity of Nigeria by advocating and facilitating the emergence of Nigerian president of Igbo stock in 2023, after 50 years after the Biafra War ended, failure to do so will undoubtedly may affect the Unity of Nigeria. A New Zik of Africa will be presented to Nigerians by 2021; Nigerians especially the youths will ensure that there will be generational shift in 2023 ,as the next president of Nigeria will not be above 65 years by 2023, Nigeria need a energetic Person with vigour to reactivate the full potentials of Nigeria as truly the Giant of Africa. 